<p class="select rel_2">
  <%= f.label :role_id, "Role" %>
  <%= f.collection_select :role_id, current_user.is_admin? ? Role.all : Role.user_roles, :id, :display_name, {:include_blank => true}, :class => "role_select" %>
</p>
<p class="select rel_1">
  <%= f.label :jurisdiction_id,  "Jurisdiction" %>
  <%= f.collection_select :jurisdiction_id, Jurisdiction.nonroot, :id, :name, {:include_blank => true}, :class => "jurisdiction_select" %>
</p>
<p class='clear'>
	Roles ensure that you receive health alerts in the jurisdictions you work in with the role that you have been assigned.
</p>
<p>
	The Public role will allow you to receive general announcements about health issues in your jurisdiction.
	You may choose to have a Public role in more than one jurisdiction.
</p>
<p>
	All roles besides Public will require authorization from an administrator in that Jurisdiction.
	You may request the role by selecting the jurisdiction and role above, and an appropriate administrator will be notified to approve the role.
	Once the role has been approved or denied, you will receive an email notifying you of this.
</p>